# What the platform is

The productized lakehouse — one place where data engineering, SQL, streaming, data science, and ML all run against a **single governed copy** of data.

## Built in three layers

1. **Open lakehouse foundation** — Delta Lake tables on your own cloud object storage, in open formats, so no vendor locks the bytes away
2. **Unified governance** — Unity Catalog governs every table, file, model, and dashboard through one permission model across all workspaces and clouds
3. **Data intelligence engine** — generative AI that reads your data's semantics, powering natural-language search, auto-optimization, and smart defaults

The payoff: one platform, one copy of data, every workload — instead of stitching a warehouse, lake, streaming, and ML system together and copying data between them.
